abstract: A new Denmark study shows that a newer generation of birth control pills poses more danger of venous thromboembolism.
snippet: A new Denmark study shows that a newer generation of birth control pills poses more danger of venous thromboembolism.
lead_paragraph: A new study of 1.3 million Danish women over nine years adds to the evidence that some newer birth-control pills, including the best-seller Yaz, have a higher risk of causing potentially dangerous blood clots.

headline.main: Study: Yaz Has Higher Risks of Blood Clots
